title.30: Darkhold: Pages from the Book of Sins (1992) #5
title.97: Darkhold: Pages from the Book of Sins (1992) #4

description.5: To everyone else, it looks like Lisa Rizzo set a local pizza shop ablaze, but Daredevil's enhanced senses see things differently. Can Daredevil solve the mystery and set an innocent life free?
description.7: Hulk inherits leadership of the Pantheon! His first mission? Travel to the Amazon rainforests where poisonous snakes aren't his worst threat. A strongman equal to the Hulk lies in wait!
description.10: Who is The Specialist? What is his connection to Alchemax? And what's his beef with Spider-Man? In this dystopian future, Spider-Man 2099 may encounter more questions than answers.
description.11: A bewitched Eric continues to rampage against Thor for the rights to Mjolnir...and Lady Sif!
description.15: Battle on two fronts! While Sue works with Johnny to clear his name, Reed and Ben fight for survival trapped in a pocket dimension! Guest-starring Silver Sable, Daredevil, and Spider-Man!
description.17: An attempt by Professor X to unlock Wolverine's dormant memories reverts Logan back to a state of mind from decades earlier. And unfortunately, that state of mind is one of a killer!
description.22: Reed Richard's plan to switch Jen and Weezi back into their own bodies fails!
description.23: The First Starring Series for Venom!  Venom escaped New York and now resides in San Francisco. Having turned over a new leaf, Venom decides to become a protector of the weak and forgotten. But can this lethal protector truly become a hero?
description.28: Moon Knight needs a replacement.  Who can fill the shoes of the Fist of Khonshu?
description.35: With a rogue Venom on the loose, Peter's nearest and dearest are far from safe. And when Peter's parents are kidnapped by Venom, Spider-Man must muster all his strength to save the family he only just met!
description.36: When the Avengers agree to help Arkon, a deadly turn may force one of the Avengers into becoming a killer as well?
description.37: Cap, Falc, and Diamond disguise themselves as villains to infiltrate the Arena of Death. But when Captain America is exposed, the Avengers face a horde of Earth's most dangerous super villains!
description.46: Spider-Man’s infamous stay in the Mad Dog Ward resumes!
description.47: Will Spidey, Blaze and Ghost Rider be able to save Hag and Troll's imprisoned humans before their life forces are devoured by Deathspawn?
description.51: It's Hulk versus Maestro, the evil future Hulk. How can the Green Goliath take down Maestro if Maestro knows every move that Hulk will make?
description.52: Introducing a new character, the Flame! When this mysterious individual wreaks havoc in the hills of Asgard, Thor rushes to stop him!
description.57: Can the combined forces of Iron Man and War Machine stop the fury of the Face Thief!?
description.60: In Brooklyn, Daredevil saves a woman from a burning building and stumbles into a tragic mystery.
description.62: The Leader has been blown to smithereens! In his place, a new villain must rise! Plus, Ironclad challenges the Hulk.
description.65: Miguel O'Hara explains how he gained his abilities to his holographic assistant Lyla. Meanwhile, Miguel must ward off the growing interest of Tyler Stone, the CEO of the mysterious Alchemax Corporation. Will Stone discover the true identity of Spider-Man?
description.66: Will Eric Masterson survive the Gauntlet? Thor Odinson is freed at last from his banishment.
description.67: Is the Realm Eternal large enough for two Thors?!
description.70: Empire State University is burning, and it's all the Human Torch's fault! Can Johnny clear his name while he's the target of a citywide manhunt?
description.72: Wolverine loses another comrade to Weapon X. Will Logan ever be able to escape his past?
description.78: Detailed technical specs and insights from Tony Stark on his many suits of armor all in one manual!
description.80: The New Warriors must deliver the news of the slain Hellions to Magma and Empath. An emotional eulogy follows.
description.82: Venom, Ghost Rider, and Johnny Blaze must team up to avoid becoming Hag and Troll's sacrifices!
description.83: Alistair Smythe, the master-mind behind the robotic attacks transforms himself into the ULTIMATE SPIDER SLAYER. Not only does Spider-Man have to worry about giant spider robots but must also face a crooked FBI agent and save his parents.
description.84: Spidey's quickly approaching a fiery death, courtesy of a crooked FBI agent. Will this mark the end of Spider-Man? And should he survive, will Peter be able to track down Alistair Smythe and his Spider-Slayers tech?
description.85: Invasion of the 6th century! Black Knight's Ebony Blade threatens to slash through the 20th century with renewed evil, after a group of medieval warriors attempt to seize the enchanted weapon for themselves!
description.86: Arkon's on a rampage in NYC and the Avengers are there to put an end to it. But is this threat from another dimension, just like the Gatherers?
description.87: It's all-out action as Cap enter the Arena of Death!
description.90: Three stories in one issue! X-Factor battles Charon, a new villain who shares history with Strong Guy. Guido saves a puppy, and each team member's backstory is revealed through a series of flashbacks! This is the tell-all issue you've been waiting to read!
description.93: Demogoblin cannot evade the Moon Knight and he will learn that Marc Spector can even make a demon cower.

0.text: Ultron and War Toy unite to take down Earth’s Mightiest, but what happens when their fighting turns internal? Ultron learns that not all is fair in love, as War Toy becomes angered with her husband and creator!

1.text: Members of X-Force are ready to break free! Meanwhile, Sunspot broods over the fate of X-Force, and Cannonball has a heated conversation with Professor X.

2.text: Drax and Arthur Douglas prove to be one in the same after Hulk tries to take away Drax’s music . Moondragon reaches a startling conclusion about her father. Two of the universes’ mightiest fighters go head-to-head!

3.text: It's all led to this! The epic showdown between Quasar and arch nemesis Blue Marvel! Imbued with the power of the Star Brand, will Quasar stand triumphant over evil?

6.text: The Warpies have Cerise and Nightcrawler hostage on Cloud Nine!

8.text: The Living Laser attacks! Determined to kill Tony Stark as revenge for his last defeat, the Laser will have to settle for Jim Rhodes in his new mirror-plated armor! Plus: Rhodey learns that Tony Stark is alive...and he isn't happy about it! (Originally published as IRON MAN (1993) #289)

16.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Epilogue. The X-Men take solace in a moment of peace as they contemplate their current situations.  What irreperable damage has Stryfe done?

20.text: Cage set-up by Troop? But why? Former allies reveal their true colors, as a gang named “Trash” takes the villainous spotlight. What does Trash want with Cage?

21.text: The Guardians of the Universe travel to battle the super-powered Badoon! Meanwhile, Aleta is back and better than ever!

22.text: Reed Richard's plan to switch Jen and Weezi back into their own bodies fails!

24.text: Fury and Captain America uncover the Hydra agents who once represented Hydra’s Inner Echelon.

25.text: Leia, Luke, Han, and Chewie make it out of Doctor Arakkus' death trap by the skin of their teeth and head for home at long last, only to discover that Rebel headquarters is under Imperial attack! Will they find safe haven with new allies on the water world of Aquaris, or will those allies turn out to be as dangerous as Darth Vader?

26.text: This issue is an Optic Blast! Can the X-Men survive the experience?!

27.text: A special anniversary issue containing THREE gritty stories with the Punisher. Featuring the conclusion to the "Police Action" storyline!

29.text: A new era begins for the Warriors as the Darkforce attacks.

30.text: The Punisher is baited with the fulfillment of his greatest wish -- the resurrection of his family. Ghost Rider and Doctor Strange guest-star!

33.text: In order to combat Dormammu in the Dark Dimension, Strange calls upon a new group of Secret Defenders for support.

39.text: Love is in the air (finally!) when Captain Britain asks Meggan to marry him! Meanwhile, Phoenix prevents Galactus from consuming an entire world.

41.text: Even a robot can love, as Ultron proves when he creates a consort by the name of War Toy. War Toy has been modeled off the brain patterns of Mockingbird; what desperate measures will Hawkeye employ to save his former wife? The return of Goliath, super-sized Clint Barton!

42.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 12. The final confrontation! Stryfe, Apocalypse, and the X-Men witness the end of X-CUTIONER'S SONG!

43.text: Before he was Drax the Destroyer, Guardian of the Galaxy, he was Arthur Douglas, a mediocre jazz musician and all-around family man. Drax travels to the deserts of Nevada after recalling his human death. The past comes flooding in, providing many painful memories for Drax and Moondragon.

44.text: Blue Marvel attempts to strike an alliance with The Punisher. Now why would anyone do a thing like that? Still in the White Room, Quasar talks life and death with fellow Protectors. Guest-starring Thanos!

46.text: Spider-Man’s infamous stay in the Mad Dog Ward resumes!

47.text: Will Spidey, Blaze and Ghost Rider be able to save Hag and Troll's imprisoned humans before their life forces are devoured by Deathspawn?

48.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 11. The X-Men launch their attempt to rescue Cyclops and Jean Grey from Stryfe's secret moon base. Just what are the connections between Cyclops, Jean, Cable, and Stryfe?

50.text: Introducing Raptor!  But will he join the Avengers West Coast or become one of their nemeses?  Plus, Ultron's mechanized evil rears his ugly face.

53.text: The introduction of Lazarus! A telekinetic villain is determined to exact revenge on all those who have caused him harm.  And all those who have yet to cross his path!

58.text: Every major being that Strange has ever called upon asks for his help in the War of Seven Spheres!

61.text: Leaving of from the previous issue, Captain, Meggan and Kitty battle and suppress Icon in Wakanda! All the while, Kurt and Cerise track down the Knight Errant who interrupted their night at the opera!

63.text: It's armored warfare times three! Iron Man, the hero trying to save the country's innocents! Atom Smasher, determined to show the world the dangers of nuclear warfare! And Firepower, ordered to stop the others at any cost! And Tony Stark regains consciousness! (Originally published as IRON MAN (1993) #288)

68.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 10. The lives of the X-Men are in the hands of their enemies! Apocalypse may be the only one who can save Professor X from the Techno-Organic Virus, while Cyclops and Jean Grey are at the mercy of Stryfe.

71.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 9. Cyclops and Jean Grey struggle to escape the deadly clutches of Stryfe, while the other X-Men find themselves in one of their most shocking alliances ever!

72.text: Wolverine loses another comrade to Weapon X. Will Logan ever be able to escape his past?

74.text: Jack of Hearts needs help from the Silver Surfer!

76.text: Who is Legacy and what is their cosmic destiny?

77.text: Magneto appears to the X-Men! Is he friend or foe!?

79.text: Two heavy-hitters, one single issue! The Hulk comes to town looking for the Rhino…and some answers. But will Luke Cage be able to talk sense into an animalistic Hulk? Not a chance.

80.text: The New Warriors must deliver the news of the slain Hellions to Magma and Empath. An emotional eulogy follows.

81.text: Major Victory and Captain America call upon Doctor Strange for some back-up!

82.text: Venom, Ghost Rider, and Johnny Blaze must team up to avoid becoming Hag and Troll's sacrifices!

85.text: Invasion of the 6th century! Black Knight’s Ebony Blade threatens to slash through the 20th century with renewed evil, after a group of medieval warriors attempt to seize the enchanted weapon for themselves!

88.text: Detailed biographies of all the characters involved in X-CUTIONER'S SONG...from villains like Apocalypse and Mr. Sinister to heroes Cyclops, Havok, Cable and more.

89.text: After his adventures with Tanith Shire and the Serpent Masters, Luke rejoins Leia on Kabal just as the planet falls under Imperial attack. Luckily, Han and Chewie come to the rescue once again, that is, until a false homing beacon leads them into a trap of stellar proportions!

91.text: S.H.I.E.L.D. Central has been destroyed! Nick Fury reports on the scene to see if there are any survivors.

92.text: V.I.G.I.L and Punisher don't have a ton in common, but one thing they share is a desire to capture one very specific criminal. Who’s going to get to the mark first?

94.text: A handful of Celtic gods need Kyllian’s help! Doctor Strange offers to teach them mystic arts as an endorsement for their cause.

95.text: Continued from New Warriors #34! An impressive array of heroes including Spider-Man, Nova and Dagger join the New Warriors to defeat an ‘Unbearable Being of Darkness’ that has overridden the powers of the Darkforce!

96.text: Dwayne Taylor stands to lose everything in “Grief, Loss and Betrayal”!

97.text: Guest-starring Sabretooth, Scarlet Witch AND the Punisher! The Redeemers must save a small town from the N'Garai demons…and even the ferocious Sabretooth acts like a team player!

98.text: Ultron has returned, and his first stop is the West Coast! With the automaton set on humanity’s extermination, will Ultron come into conflict with the West Coast Avengers? You bet!

99.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 8. A major secret about Cable's past is revealed! Stryfe vs. Apocalyse in a villain vs. villain throw down!
